Python (OpenAI-style API)

python
from openai import OpenAI

client = OpenAI(api_key="your_api_key")

response = client.chat.completions.create(
    model="gpt-4.1-mini",
    messages=[
        {"role": "system", "content": "You are a helpful assistant"},
        {"role": "user", "content": "Extract name and date from: John met Mary on June 2."}
    ],
    temperature=0
)

print(response.choices[0].message.content)

Example with Structured Output Prompt

python
prompt = """
Extract name and date. Return JSON only.

Text: John met Mary on June 2.
"""

response = client.chat.completions.create(
    model="gpt-4.1-mini",
    messages=[{"role": "user", "content": prompt}],
    temperature=0
)

print(response.choices[0].message.content)

CURL Example

BASH
curl https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "model": "gpt-4.1-mini",
    "messages": [
      {"role": "user", "content": "Summarize AI in one sentence"}
    ]
  }'

